Forwarded from: Competition of young international workers of the CIS named after. Andrey Gromyko
Applications are still being accepted for the A.A. Gromyko Competition of Young CIS International Workers - 2024. The competition is open to students and graduates of higher education institutions, graduate students, scientists, teachers, journalists, analysts, business specialists, representatives of public organizations, diplomats - historians, economists, political scientists, lawyers, sociologists, philosophers.🗓To participate in the competition, you must submit an application on the website by May 13, 2024, attaching your unpublished scientific article or journalistic essay.✏️Topics of scientific articles:• Prospects for integration projects in the post-Soviet space: Union the state of Belarus and Russia, the EAEU, the CIS, the CSTO;
• Contours of the new world order: challenges and opportunities for Russia and the CIS countries;
• Scientific diplomacy as a resource for the formation of Greater Eurasia;
• “Total sanctions war”: legal status, consequences and methods of counteraction;
• The role and place of Central Asia and Transcaucasia in Eurasian integration;
• Threats of conflicts and tools for strengthening security in Eurasia;
• Diplomatic legacy of A.A. Gromyko;
• The Great Patriotic War and the Second World War: the problem of preserving historical memory and the fight against falsification of history;
• The role of the UN, its past and future in the system of international relations.✏️Topics of journalistic essays:• “A new redistribution of the world: a war of civilizations or a balance of macro-regions?”;
• “Culture wars”: how does the struggle to reformat human identity affect world politics?

The works of the competition finalists will be published in a scientific collection of articles, the winners - in leading scientific journals, incl. included in the list of Higher Attestation Commissions. The winners in the main category will receive valuable prizes - a laptop, tablet or smartphone. The debut category includes a smart watch, fitness bracelet or external hard drive. There are also prizes in special categories decided by the jury.

45 finalists will be invited to the final of the competition at the Institute of Europe of the Russian Academy of Sciences and MGIMO University of the Russian Foreign Ministry.

Based on the results of the debates, during which the works will be defended at the Competition Finalists Forum, the Jury can provide the winners with:
• Grant for a research project, publication of a monograph or participation in a conference in Russia.
• Grant for advanced training at leading Russian universities, including MGIMO.
• Letter of recommendation for an internship at the Eurasian Economic Commission, MGIMO.

Additional information can be found in the Competition Regulations. You can find out more on our YouTube channel and VKontakte page. Organizers: Association of Foreign Policy Research named after A.A. Gromyko, MGIMO Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, Academy of Management under the President of the Republic of Belarus and the Institute of Europe of the Russian Academy of Sciences with the support of the Permanent Committee of the Union State, the Eurasian Economic Commission, MFGS CIS.konkurs-gromyko.orgCompetition of young internationalists of the CIS named after A. A. GromykoThe competition accepts articles and journalistic essays students, university graduates, graduate students, scientists, teachers, analysts and diplomats
